Detailed Description

Interface toward europa.

Interface with europa.

This class connects to europa components manipulated by TREX

Author:
Conor Mcgann & Frederic Py <fpy@mbari.org>

This class is used by a EuropaReactor and all its related classes as en entry point to the eeuropa plan data base and solvers. It gives access to europa constructs along with TREX specific entities inside the europa framework.

Author:
Conor McGann & Frederic Py <fpy@mbari.org>

bool TREX::europa::Assembly::active (  )  const [inline]

Check if active.

This method indicates if the Assembly deliberation state is active. Being active means that the current plan database of the assembly is not yet complete (meaning that there are still flaws to be resolved in the plan)

Return values:
true if this assembly deliberation state is active

Definition at line 253 of file Assembly.hh.

std::pair<EUROPA::ObjectId, EUROPA::TokenId> TREX::europa::Assembly::convert ( TREX::transaction::Predicate const &  pred,
bool  isFact = false 
)

Convert TREX ptredicate into an europa token.

Parameters:
[in] pred A trex predicate
[in] isFact Fact flag

Convert pred as a europa token which is either a fact -- if isFact is true -- or a rejectable goal -- if isFact is false.

Precondition:
pred.object() is a valid AgentTimline in the loaded model
Returns:
A pair with second referring to the newly created token and first referrign to the timeline this token is attached to.
Note:
If the predicate name does not exist for the object of this predicate. The output will depend on isFact :
  • if isFact is true then this function will create the special UNDEFINED_PRED token.
  • if isFact is false it will not create a new token and will return a pair of noId() instead
Exceptions:
EuropaException Unable to create the UNDEFINED_PRED token
See also:
UNDEFINED_PRED
EUROPA::ConstrainedVariableId TREX::europa::Assembly::default_pred ( EUROPA::ObjectId const &  obj  )  const [inline]

Access object default predicate.

Parameters:
[in] obj A europa object
Precondition:
obj is an AgentTimeline

This method extract the default predicate attribute of obj.

The default predicate of an AgentTimeline is the default token type that would be produced in case the solver is not able to identify the current state of this variabale.

Exceptions:
EuropaException obj does not have a default predicate
Returns:
The europa variable representing the default for obj

bool Assembly::isInternal ( EUROPA::ObjectId const &  obj  )  const

Check if internal.

Parameters:
[in] obj An object

Check if obj is a trex Internal timeline.

Note:
This checking is at the reactor level -- and not simply at the model level. Indeed, it may happen that a timeline has been specified as Internal by the model but was already owned by another reactor. In that case a warning message would have been displayed in TREX.log and this timeline mode would have been set as Private and this method will return false
Bug:
I am not sure that this policy to migrate a timline from Internal o Private is the good one. It may be better to demote failed Internal timelines to External until we can take ownership of this timeline ...
Return values:
true if obj is a trex Internal timeline
false otherwise
See also:
isExternal(EUROPA::ObjectId const &) const
isIgnored(EUROPA::ObjectId const &) const

void TREX::europa::Assembly::setStream (  ) 

Switch europa debug stream.

Set the europa debug stream toward the fille associated to this Assembly. Europa logging mechanism is tied to the global process but can be changed on the fly. We use this ability to be ebale to distribute logging messages in one fule per deliberative reactor. This method is called to ensure that future messages produced by europa logging (debugMsg) will all be redirected to the file associated to this assembly.

Postcondition:
all europa debug messages are now redirected toward the file associated to this assembly

EUROPA::LabelStr const TREX::europa::Assembly::PRIVATE_MODE [static]

Nddl private mode value.

The symbolic name used in europa model to specify a trex timeline as Private.

A Private timeline is owned by this reactor but not made publicly available for other reactors -- therefore acting as any europa timeline which is not an AgentTimeline. Such construct is usefull when someone wants to use an AgentTimeline but does not want to have this timeline constrainted by TREX requirements on shared timelines.

Note:
While his construct is not really necessary anymore in this version of TREX (as it supports basic europa timelines). It can proves convenient when a timeline specified as a TREX timeline needs to be used by a reactor without the need to publish it to other reactors.
